olive oil
1 packet Fusilli
1 stalk Celery
2 packet Beef & Pork Mince
1 sachet Nan's Special Seasoning
½ packet Cream
1 sachet Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 packet Chargrilled Capsicum Relish
1 packet Baby Leaves

• Boil the kettle. Half-fill a large saucepan with boiling water, then add a generous pinch of salt.
• Cook fusilli uncovered, over high heat, until °al dente°, 12 minutes.
• Reserve some of the pasta water (1/2 cup for 2 people / 1 cup for 4 people), drain and return to saucepan.

• Meanwhile, finely chop celery.
• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over high heat. Cook celery and beef & pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.

• Add Aussie spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add cream (see ingredients), chicken-style stock powder and reserved pasta water (cup for 2 people / cup for 4 people), and cook, stirring, until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then add chargrilled capsicum relish, cooked fusilli and baby leaves. Stir to combine.

• Divide creamy beef and pork fusilli between bowls. Enjoy!